</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,258,1075]" box="[199,387,834,859]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,262,834,859]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Host.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="39" pageNumber="40" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,258,1075]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,870,895]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Etymology.</emphasis>
An adjective from Latin meaning &quot;combed&quot; referring to the setal combs on the posterior of the abdomen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
